\begin_layout Standard
Figure 1 shows Algorithm 2 applied to the FoodAPS data.
 Over half of households can be described by a single utility function;
 there are 5-10 sizable groups,
 and the remainder are very small.
 Table 2 shows summary statistics for milk purchases by group;
 the descriptive statistics already illustrate significant heterogeneity in behavior across types.
 For example,
 Type 1 favors whole milk,
 Type 2 favors 2% milk,
 and Type 3 almost exclusively purchases 1% milk.
\end_layout

