\begin_layout Standard
Figure 2 shows the schedule of rationality and types.
 At 15 types,
 the data are fully rationalized:
 every group has a CCEI of 1.
 Combining all households into one type results in significant irrationality (that is,
 significant individual heterogeneity).
 In between,
 the schedule shows exactly how much rationality each additional type buys,
 and we can reduce the number of types substantially while keeping every group close to rational.
 Informally,
 it is 
\emph on
approximately correct
\emph default
 to treat the households within each group as sharing the same utility function.

